        }
      ],
      "message": "init: Reserve file descriptors for IPC connections\n\nWhen -ipcbind is used, the node opens one listening socket FD per\nbound address, plus accepts up to N concurrent IPC connections. Neither\nwas previously accounted for in min_required_fds, meaning IPC-heavy\nworkloads could silently exhaust available file descriptors.\n\nThis adds -ipcmaxconnections (default: 16, mirroring -rpcworkqueue) to\nlet operators control the FD reservation, and adds nIpcBind to account\nfor the listening socket FDs.\n\nSuggested by Sjors in #32297.",
      "committer": {
        "name": "Enoch Azariah",
        "email": "enirox001@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-04-01T08:04:44Z"
      },
